3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to evaluate natural language generation systems. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper may discuss the use of neural networks in natural language generation and evaluation. 
5. cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely sub-category as the paper may discuss the development of software tools for natural language generation and evaluation.
